<div id="review_1730829411" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1730829411" />
    <a title="Simon" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7232880-simon"><img alt="Simon" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1546303611p2/7232880.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1730829411?book_show_action=true">Aug 17, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Simon" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Simon" href="/user/show/7232880-simon">Simon</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781780745879" href="/book/show/22912371-a-brief-history-of-seven-killings">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1730829411" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4762616002662135674">What a book. Almost a year after it won the Booker and The Green Carnation Prize, which I founded, and I have finally read it. It&apos;s not been an easy read, it&apos;s not been a pleasant read but it&apos;s a fantastic read. Gritty, violent, thought provoking, confronting and a real challenge but I&apos;ve come away from it feeling as enriched and shocked as I have put through the ringer. I need more time with my thoughts. </span>
  <span id="freeText4762616002662135674" style="display:none">What a book. Almost a year after it won the Booker and The Green Carnation Prize, which I founded, and I have finally read it. It's not been an easy read, it's not been a pleasant read but it's a fantastic read. Gritty, violent, thought provoking, confronting and a real challenge but I've come away from it feeling as enriched and shocked as I have put through the ringer. I need more time with my thoughts. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4762616002662135674" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


